verses.verse: The <S%H3068>Lord<s%> <S%H4427>reigns,<s%> He is <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H1348>majesty;<s%> The <S%H3068>Lord<s%> has <S%H3847>clothed<s%> and <S%H247>girded<s%> Himself with <S%H5797>strength;<s%> <S%H637>Indeed,<s%> the <S%H8398>world<s%> is <S%H3559>firmly<s%> <S%H3559>established,<s%> it will not be <S%H4131>moved.<s%>
Thy <S%H3678>throne<s%> is <S%H3559>established<s%> from of <S%H9241>old;<s%> Thou art from <S%H5769>everlasting.<s%>

The <S%H5104>floods<s%> have <S%H5375>lifted<s%> up, O <S%H3068>Lord,<s%> The <S%H5104>floods<s%> have <S%H5375>lifted<s%> up their <S%H6963>voice;<s%> The <S%H5104>floods<s%> <S%H5375>lift<s%> up their <S%H1796>pounding<s%> <S%H1796>waves.<s%>

<S%H4480>More<s%> <S%H4480>than<s%> the <S%H6963>sounds<s%> of <S%H7227>many<s%> <S%H4325>waters,<s%> [Than] the <S%H117>mighty<s%> <S%H4867>breakers<s%> of the <S%H3220>sea,<s%> The <S%H3068>Lord<s%> on <S%H4791>high<s%> is <S%H117>mighty.<s%>
